Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 996 "The \NSkilled Hawk Hides His Crimes"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[OP]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,[ED]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,[Eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.48,0:00:09.48,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to\NTraditional-style House Café\NTakehara
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.33,0:00:22.34,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,A falcon? No, is it an eagle?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.34,0:00:23.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a hawk.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.48,0:00:26.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a raptor called a Harris's hawk.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.19,0:00:27.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Move.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.81,0:00:30.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes are like mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.67,0:00:32.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They're sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.53,0:00:39.60,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You'll stress out the hawk \Nif you point or wave at him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.97,0:00:39.60,Tetsu,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Akashiba Tetsu (28) \NFalconer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.93,0:00:42.60,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Hawks are delicate creatures!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.60,0:00:43.81,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.16,0:00:46.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.39,0:00:51.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Your fault for showing off, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.96,0:00:55.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Find the question that solves the mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.70,0:00:57.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apply miraculous detective skills \Nto the secrets of the heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.96,0:00:59.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A traditional-style home \Ncafé holds a falconry event.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.98,0:01:02.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Determine the trick using your keen eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.30,0:01:04.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.04,0:01:05.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.80,0:01:08.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.06,0:02:54.06,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(399,1)}The Skilled Hawk Hides His Crimes
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.89,0:02:51.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Skilled Hawk Hides His Crimes!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.06,0:02:57.07,Welcome,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to \NTraditional-style House Café \NTakehara
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.27,0:03:13.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really holding some kind of festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.58,0:03:13.58,Schedule,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,13:00 \NPuffed rice making event \N13:30 \NPuffed rice complete \N15:00 \NFalconry experience event \N16:00 \NFalconry main event
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.84,0:03:13.58,Festival,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Okuho Mountain Village Festival
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.92,0:03:17.38,Masahiko,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Ishima Masahiko (50) \NFarmer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.97,0:03:17.88,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You're lucky. You have the whole \Nplace to yourselves today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.23,0:03:19.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.88,0:03:22.36,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Here's your tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.51,0:03:28.97,Satoko,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Takehara Satoko (35) \NGenichi's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.94,0:03:30.19,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's quiet today, but this place \Nwas thriving until recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.97,0:03:34.05,DCItalic,REPORTER,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to introduce Takehara Genichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.05,0:03:37.87,DCItalic,REPORTER,0000,0000,0000,,He quit his office job to open \Na traditional-style home café,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.86,0:03:41.28,Genichi,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Takehara Genichi (37) \NCafé Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.87,0:03:41.04,DCMain,REPORTER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and is currently holding an event \Nto revitalize his mountain village.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.61,0:03:47.41,DCItalic,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Serene and beautiful mountain villages have \Nthe mysterious ability to soothe people's hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.88,0:03:52.06,DCItalic,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I began this event because I wanted \Nmore people to learn about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.26,0:03:54.85,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.85,0:03:58.62,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Experiencing an event while surrounded \Nby nature does seem like it would
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.62,0:04:02.42,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,produce memories a little \Ndifferent from one's everyday life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.12,0:04:04.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.51,0:04:05.18,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.92,0:04:09.58,DCMain,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I told you not to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.58,0:04:13.56,DCMain,REALTOR,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I forgot to get \Nyour signature in one spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.40,0:04:20.44,DCMain,REALTOR,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't told anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.71,0:04:23.56,DCMain,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I told my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.96,0:04:25.96,DCMain,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to tell anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.48,0:04:29.33,DCMain,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,They'd probably kill me if I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.94,0:04:32.11,DCMain,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Here. How's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.88,0:04:34.33,DCMain,REALTOR,0000,0000,0000,,Good, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.57,0:04:41.34,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn't a customer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.34,0:04:43.76,DCMain,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,No. Apparently he was lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.76,0:04:45.33,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.66,0:04:50.35,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Honey, could we get some boar?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.35,0:04:51.56,DCMain,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.14,0:04:53.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Boar?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.93,0:04:55.69,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you like Botan stew?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.88,0:04:58.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Botan stew? I love Botan stew.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.45,0:05:03.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Botan stew is made with boar meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.41,0:05:07.33,DCMain,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I'm able to catch one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.33,0:05:09.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.33,0:05:15.82,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.55,0:05:17.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.66,0:05:19.56,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.94,0:05:27.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, this is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.46,0:05:29.48,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I made it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.48,0:05:33.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Wait, did you make everything here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.07,0:05:40.21,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I made all the animals in the café.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.78,0:05:43.04,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,When my husband quit his office job,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.04,0:05:46.25,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,he asked me to open this café with him,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.25,0:05:48.94,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,so I quit my office job, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.94,0:05:52.37,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But this was my only skill,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.37,0:05:54.91,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,so I made these while running the café.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.62,0:05:59.12,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,These animals are the physical \Nrepresentation of the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.12,0:06:01.54,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and memories I made working at this café.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.26,0:06:04.00,DCMain,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.69,0:06:09.83,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.83,0:06:11.68,DCMain,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.68,0:06:13.18,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.52,0:06:17.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck with your hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.15,0:06:18.32,DCMain,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.81,0:06:21.81,Festival,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Okuho Mountain Village Festival
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.81,0:06:21.81,Schedule,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,13:00 \NPuffed rice making event \N13:30 \NPuffed rice complete
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.24,0:06:24.82,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,This rice came from my fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.58,0:06:28.10,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's feed this into the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.63,0:06:31.70,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Then we close the lid, light the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.18,0:06:37.83,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,and turn it while waiting \Nfor the pressure to rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.19,0:06:42.21,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I used to go into the \Ncity to sell puffed rice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.78,0:06:45.88,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Tons of kids around your age would gather.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.88,0:06:48.06,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,It was a lot of fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.49,0:06:54.22,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,But now I'm the only one in this \Narea who makes puffed rice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.50,0:06:58.48,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,The other farmers who grew \Nrice quit farming, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.89,0:07:05.23,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm grateful to Genichi-san for allowing \Nme to make puffed rice at this café.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.50,0:07:07.46,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm truly grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.50,0:07:11.53,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Once the pressure is high enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.74,0:07:14.74,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,we close the lid so the puffed \Nrice doesn't go flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.51,0:07:18.96,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Right on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.96,0:07:19.75,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.10,0:07:22.12,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.21,0:07:33.05,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.40,0:07:36.76,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,You look like a dove that's \Nbeen shot by a pea shooter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.38,0:07:40.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was a bit loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.05,0:07:44.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I think I just heard a gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.56,0:07:52.11,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, we coat the rice with \Nsugar water and mix well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.71,0:07:54.23,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,And it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.81,0:07:56.58,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Eat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.14,0:08:02.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.26,0:08:06.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Is that her husband?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.14,0:08:07.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.43,0:08:11.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Bring us a nice juicy boar!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.88,0:08:17.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.35,0:08:23.10,Festival,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Okuho Mountain Village Festival
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.35,0:08:23.10,Schedule,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,13:00 \NPuffed rice making event \N13:30 \NPuffed rice complete \N15:00 \NFalconry experience event \N16:00 \NFalconry main event
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.79,0:08:25.98,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,L-Like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.38,0:08:29.17,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,You're okay. Try to relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.62,0:08:32.59,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Hawks can sense your nervousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.10,0:08:34.31,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.97,0:08:35.86,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.10,0:08:38.37,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Now pick up the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.60,0:08:39.42,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.16,0:08:46.60,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.90,0:08:59.27,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I did it. I did it, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.27,0:09:01.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing, Ran-neechan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.46,0:09:03.71,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, you're next. Give it a shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.71,0:09:04.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.29,0:09:06.76,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.76,0:09:08.44,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.71,0:09:10.65,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,You're scared of hawks, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.65,0:09:11.32,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.32,0:09:12.67,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.59,0:09:15.45,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I like birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.45,0:09:19.50,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Among them, raptors are my \Nfavorite, especially hawks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.50,0:09:22.26,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I started this job.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.97,0:09:27.73,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Things are quiet now, but lots \Nof people used to come before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.73,0:09:30.84,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,It was fun and felt worthwhile.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.09,0:09:36.22,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hoping to liven up this place \Nwith this guy like we used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.46,0:09:42.47,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,So if you could promote \Ntoday's event at school,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.86,0:09:44.42,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.02,0:09:45.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.82,0:09:47.10,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.68,0:09:55.40,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, why don't you try it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.66,0:09:58.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I'm not interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.44,0:10:00.77,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's because he got yelled at earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.41,0:10:04.09,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,This concludes the falconry show.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.09,0:10:05.85,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Botan stew is next.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.85,0:10:07.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Now this is what I've been waiting for!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.03,0:10:09.29,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.29,0:10:11.34,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't done that yet, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.48,0:10:13.84,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What haven't we done?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.02,0:10:17.84,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The main event of our café's \NOkuho Mountain Village Festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.34,0:10:21.15,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,We send the hawk to the target over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.14,0:10:34.23,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,There's a lure with rabbit fur and meat \Nhanging in a clearing on that mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.50,0:10:37.46,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We have him fly all the way there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.46,0:10:40.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Seems pretty far. Can he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.52,0:10:42.52,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.64,0:11:04.39,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Is that my husband?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.07,0:11:06.11,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.11,0:11:07.27,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.75,0:11:08.64,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.00,0:11:15.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Sir. Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.98,0:11:16.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.13,0:11:26.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately... Ran, call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.68,0:11:27.87,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.04,0:11:30.92,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,No. Honey...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.36,0:11:34.04,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.53,0:11:44.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was it accidentally fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.00,0:11:50.27,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So, Mori-kun, you're saying \Nit was an accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.46,0:11:51.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.12,0:11:56.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The victim Takehara Genichi-san was \Ninside the thicket with a shotgun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.94,0:11:59.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The hawk attacked him in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.61,0:12:05.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Genichi-san fired his shotgun \Nin an attempt to defend himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.38,0:12:10.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, the shell unfortunately \Nstruck Genichi-san himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.46,0:12:11.62,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,That's not possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.17,0:12:15.75,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,A hawk would never attack a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.22,0:12:18.37,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Hawks are afraid of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.37,0:12:22.13,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Not just hawks. Most animals are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.56,0:12:24.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But what if a gun were pointed at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.96,0:12:29.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You said just pointing at a hawk \Nwith your finger is a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.37,0:12:31.89,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I did say that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.32,0:12:34.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I saw something shining around here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.99,0:12:38.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,when the hawk changed direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.61,0:12:39.95,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Shining?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.95,0:12:43.78,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me. Did you find anything \Naround here that shines?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.14,0:12:45.68,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.68,0:12:47.28,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Not particularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.81,0:12:51.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it was the sunlight \Nreflecting off his shotgun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.80,0:12:56.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mori-kun, unlike other guns, \Nshotguns have long barrels.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.63,0:13:00.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Is it possible for someone to accidentally \Nshoot themselves with one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.49,0:13:03.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I think this is an exceptional case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.78,0:13:07.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He probably held the gun \Nlike this, then this,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.53,0:13:09.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and from here, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.44,0:13:11.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And finally, this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.31,0:13:12.94,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.69,0:13:15.12,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.12,0:13:18.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, how's the wife doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.28,0:13:22.57,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,She seems okay, but there's no \Ntelling how she really feels.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.84,0:13:24.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.89,0:13:52.10,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.41,0:13:57.10,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I know Genichi-san won't come back \Nno matter how much I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.33,0:14:00.44,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.44,0:14:02.68,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it, Akashiba-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.68,0:14:03.98,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.44,0:14:06.80,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.80,0:14:10.37,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't blame yourself or your hawk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.78,0:14:11.67,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.24,0:14:14.85,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Akashiba-kun, listen to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.85,0:14:18.12,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,She's having the hardest \Ntime dealing with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.27,0:14:20.04,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,A-All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.04,0:14:24.30,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,This is probably the last \Nyear we'll hold this event.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.30,0:14:25.22,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody will come after this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.22,0:14:27.68,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,No! We have to keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.68,0:14:31.96,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,My husband won't be able to \Nrest in peace if we stop now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.05,0:14:54.78,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.10,0:14:56.66,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.66,0:14:57.29,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.52,0:14:59.85,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to kill your hawk, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.85,0:15:01.92,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.32,0:15:06.09,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I started this job because I love hawks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.09,0:15:08.61,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,No falconer would kill his own hawk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.10,0:15:11.12,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's that medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.12,0:15:13.14,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.55,0:15:16.85,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,It's for his injured foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.57,0:15:19.28,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.66,0:15:21.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How was he injured?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.52,0:15:22.91,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.91,0:15:26.91,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,But ankle injuries can be fatal to hawks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.91,0:15:28.69,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad it wasn't serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.03,0:15:32.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When do hawks injure their ankles?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.78,0:15:35.15,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,There can be a lot of causes,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.15,0:15:39.44,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,like getting caught in crow \Nguards or fishing line.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.90,0:15:51.60,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,These two were stuck together.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.13,0:15:54.76,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. I know the approximate shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.40,0:15:58.47,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.61,0:16:01.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.24,0:16:06.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.81,0:16:24.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You made all of these, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.89,0:16:27.30,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.30,0:16:28.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're quite dexterous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.91,0:16:30.96,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm good at woodworking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.02,0:16:37.92,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Have some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.92,0:16:39.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.04,0:16:42.67,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure, we're ready to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.67,0:16:43.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.77,0:16:46.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we'll get going, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.85,0:16:56.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we were leaving...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.51,0:16:59.96,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun, could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.96,0:17:03.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, could you gather everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.73,0:17:05.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I have something important to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.97,0:17:07.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.29,0:17:07.79,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.52,0:17:13.30,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,What important thing did you want to discuss?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.54,0:17:17.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Genichi-san didn't die in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.66,0:17:18.93,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.10,0:17:23.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A device was used to disguise \Nhis death as an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.45,0:17:25.44,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What device?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.61,0:17:29.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There was fishing line strung \Nup where the husband died.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.47,0:17:34.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The hawk flew off course because \Nits feet got caught on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.32,0:17:41.59,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mori-san, we didn't find \Nany fishing line at the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.59,0:17:43.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was at the bottom of a nearby \Nravine, wrapped around a wooden drum.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.78,0:17:47.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit must've wrapped the \Nfishing line around the drum
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.05,0:17:54.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and dropped it down the ravine so it \Nwouldn't remain at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.78,0:17:57.47,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But what was the fishing line for?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.90,0:18:00.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,To fire a shotgun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.89,0:18:04.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The thread was tied to a \Nshotgun set up in the thicket.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.03,0:18:08.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The thread was drawn in \Nfront of the hawk's target.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.85,0:18:11.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When the hawk's feet got caught in the line,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.26,0:18:15.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,it pulled the trigger on the shotgun,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.92,0:18:17.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,firing a shell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.14,0:18:23.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That shell pierced the fastener on the \Ndevice supporting Genichi-san's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.06,0:18:26.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,With the fastener gone, it began to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.44,0:18:34.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It pushed Genichi-san's body out of the thicket,\Nwhile the device itself fell down the ravine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.47,0:18:39.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The shotgun was also dragged down by the \Nfishing line and left at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.27,0:18:42.65,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But Mori-san, why did the \Nculprit set up that device?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.65,0:18:44.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,To create an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.53,0:18:48.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Genichi-san was murdered before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.48,0:18:50.19,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,When was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.34,0:18:52.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When the puffed rice was made.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.32,0:18:56.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The events of this festival \Noccur at fixed times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.61,0:19:01.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Ishima-san, who is in charge of the puffed \Nrice demonstration, was exactly on schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.76,0:19:10.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit knew this and killed the husband \Nas the puffed rice machine made a loud noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.76,0:19:15.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, I thought I heard a gunshot \Nin what I believed to be an echo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.18,0:19:19.72,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Bring us a nice juicy boar!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.92,0:19:26.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But there was no echo when I shouted to \Nthe person I thought was the husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.66,0:19:30.89,DCMain,ISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Then who waved to us then?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.12,0:19:32.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.40,0:19:40.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And the person absent at \Nthat time was you, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.53,0:19:41.38,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.38,0:19:42.53,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.92,0:19:46.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You thought you could disguise the gunshot
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.25,0:19:50.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,if you shot him during the puffed \Nrice demonstration, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.39,0:19:52.92,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.09,0:19:54.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.03,0:19:57.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's that red stain on your neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.60,0:20:04.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's was a bloodstain on the \Nsame spot on your husband's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.57,0:20:08.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The blood was also on your \Nhusband's hunting jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.43,0:20:15.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It probably stained the \Nsame spot when you wore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.70,0:20:20.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have more excuses?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.75,0:20:25.57,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,No. I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.01,0:20:28.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Could you tell us why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.86,0:20:33.33,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He was trying to sell this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.61,0:20:35.94,DCItalic,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,How's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.86,0:20:41.21,DCItalic,REALTOR,0000,0000,0000,,Good. That seals our sale agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.21,0:20:42.09,DCItalic,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.36,0:20:45.15,DCItalic,REALTOR,0000,0000,0000,,I should get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.72,0:20:46.72,DCItalic,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.28,0:20:49.85,DCItalic,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm selling this place and starting over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.08,0:20:51.24,DCItalic,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,We can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.24,0:20:53.59,DCItalic,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,We built this place together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.59,0:20:55.11,DCItalic,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,And the others...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.11,0:20:56.21,DCItalic,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.21,0:20:57.54,DCItalic,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk back to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.96,0:20:59.86,DCItalic,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.38,0:21:04.11,DCItalic,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pack the animals and our things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.45,0:21:07.44,DCItalic,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.92,0:21:10.74,DCItalic,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm leaving you and the café.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.13,0:21:12.78,DCItalic,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.78,0:21:16.34,DCItalic,GENICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Both you and this café are a burden to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.00,0:21:22.52,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think he was like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.52,0:21:27.51,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought if I killed that man using the \Nmountain village's power that he mocked,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.51,0:21:30.51,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,then that poor hawk who \Nwas simply used for profit
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.91,0:21:33.92,DCMain,SATOKO,0000,0000,0000,,would be repaid in some way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.98,0:21:42.66,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, you can tell us \Nabout it at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.66,0:21:44.65,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Come with us, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.84,0:23:21.29,DCItalic,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Exterminating crows is an \Nimportant job falconers perform.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.64,0:23:24.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.00,0:23:25.17,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.86,0:23:29.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hawk!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.80,0:23:40.76,DCMain,AKASHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Hawks don't attack people, \Nbut crows do, so be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.17,0:23:42.18,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.18,0:23:44.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Should've left them alone!
